To build on previous messages, your bank account is a nominative data, so the bank's website will of course know *who you are*, the only point is that they won't know *where you are connectiong from*.

If you use Tails and so Tor, you datas will be routed through differents relays in order to hide the geographical place you are connecting from. The last relay, called exit node, can eventually catch you datas, even when you are using secured connections with SSL. This is called a [[Man in the Middle attack|doc/about/warning/#index3h1]].

--mike
